cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is about aspect term extraction (ATE) for performing aspect-based sentiment analysis. ATE is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of review corpora and attention mechanisms, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DS.
